================================================================================
SUMMARY OF CHANGES (resolving the errors above + Exercise 1 review fixes)
NOTE: could not build/promote locally (no opam switch here has core/async).
Run `dune build`, then `dune runtest` + `dune promote` to lock expect output.
================================================================================

--- Part 1: compile errors from the log above ---

* lib/order_book/src/order_book.{ml,mli}
  - `remove'` now returns `Order.t option`; added public `remove` (unit).
  - mli `For_testing.remove` -> `t -> Order_id.t -> Order.t option`.
* lib/order_book/src/matching_engine.ml
  - Fixed `resting_client_order_id` to use `Order.client_order_id resting`
    (was `order`).
* Added `client_order_id` (and Fill's aggressor_/resting_client_order_id) to
  every record literal that needed it; added Cancel_reject / Cancel arms to
  pattern matches:
    app/bots/test/test_bots.ml (filled empty `client_order_id =`),
    lib/types/test/test_order.ml, lib/types/test/test_fill.ml,
    lib/test_harness/src/harness.ml, lib/order_book/test/test_order_book.ml,
    lib/order_book/bench/bench_order_book.ml, lib/gateway/test/test_protocol.ml,
    app/monitor/src/event_log.ml (Cancel_reject in Category/Color),
    app/client/bin/main.ml (Cancel case), test_exchange_command.ml (Cancel case).
* lib/test_harness/src/e2e_helpers.ml: login_rpc now returns Or_error -> `>>| ok_exn`.

--- Part 2: Exercise 1 (1a-1g) review fixes ---
Design calls applied (all exercise-implied): cancel/dedup in the matching
engine; reject 2nd login of a live name; client order ids reserved for life;
removed the `as <name>` text clause.

* matching_engine.{ml,mli}: engine owns (participant -> client_order_id ->
  Order.t) table; submit dedups synchronously (-> Order_reject); ids never
  freed; new `cancel ~participant ~client_order_id` checks the BOOK for
  liveness (filled/missing -> Cancel_reject, else Order_cancel + BBO).
* exchange_server.ml (rewritten): request pipe carries `command = Submit |
  Cancel`; both RPCs enqueue-and-return; matching loop runs them through the
  engine. Login now: validation -> Error (not raise); rejects a 2nd live login
  with Error; registers ONE session and stores that same session in conn state
  (fixes feed delivering nothing). Removed inline cancel + vestigial event pipe.
* dispatcher.{ml,mli}: table is now `Session.t Participant.Table.t`;
  clean_up_session removes the entry (phys_equal-guarded); added find_session;
  removed state_table.
* DELETED lib/gateway/src/participant_state.{ml,mli} (now dead).
* rpc_protocol.ml: names "cancel-reject"->"cancel-order", "sesion-feed"->"session-feed".
* exchange_command.ml: dropped the `as <name>` clause.
* app/server/bin/main.ml: connect_as now logs in. app/client/bin/main.ml:
  login surfaces failure (`>>| ok_exn`) + help text updated.
* lib/gateway/test/test_rpc_shapes.ml: fixed cancel-order block (regular Rpc,
  not Pipe_rpc) + filled session-feed block.
* lib/test_harness/src/harness.ml: builders hand out UNIQUE client ids so the
  engine's dedup doesn't reject harness-driven multi-order tests.
* test_exchange_command.ml: rewritten for new grammar (no `as`, id required) +
  CANCEL tests. test_protocol.ml: round-trip parse input updated.

